Package com.novicki.easylogger.logger

Class Log

java.lang.Object
com.novicki.easylogger.logger.Log
public class Log extends Object
Logs information to the console. Logs can be in the form of error, debug, info, verbose, warning, and wtf. Each type of log requires a tag, that is indexed to be searchable, and a message, which is output to the console. Each log has a timestamp in the form yyyy/MM/dd HH:mm:ss.
Author:
Calvin Novicki

  • Constructor Details

    • Log

      private Log()
      Creates the log directory in the user.home directory if it does not exist. Then is creates a file called data.log if it does not exists, and if it does, then it copies the contents of that file to another log file with the date and time, then creates a new data.log file.

  • Method Details

    • printToLogFile

      private static void printToLogFile(String data)
      Prints data to a log file located in user.home/logs. If there is more than one log statement, the log gets appended to the existing file.
